## Output Criteria

<!-- Binary checks against what the skill PRODUCES when run on a test prompt. -->

- [ ] **EVAL-O01:** SKILL.md uses flow-graph structure, not prose
  - **Test:** Verify `## Entry`, `## Flow`, and at least one `### [ID] Name` node with `Do:` / `Exit:` sections. No sequential numbered paragraphs replacing node structure.
  - **Fail signal:** SKILL.md body is organized as numbered steps or paragraphs instead of labeled nodes.

- [ ] **EVAL-O02:** Every flow node has at least one Exit edge with an explicit condition
  - **Test:** For each `### [ID]` node, confirm `Exit:` exists and every edge follows `→ [ID] : <condition>`.
  - **Fail signal:** Any node missing `Exit:`, or any edge written without a condition clause.

- [ ] **EVAL-O03:** SKILL.md frontmatter contains all required fields with valid taxonomy values
  - **Test:** Extract YAML frontmatter. Verify required fields. Cross-check `domain` and `intent` against `taxonomy/SKILL_TAXONOMY.md`.
  - **Fail signal:** Any required field absent, or domain/intent values not in SKILL_TAXONOMY.md.

- [ ] **EVAL-O04:** `description` field is a routing contract, not a workflow summary
  - **Test:** Ask: "Could someone follow this as a replacement for reading the body?" If it describes steps or outputs rather than trigger conditions, it fails.
  - **Fail signal:** Description contains workflow language, phases, or internal vocabulary.

- [ ] **EVAL-O05:** MUST/MUST NOT use commitment language; Don't sections use imperative voice
  - **Test:** Verify MUST/MUST NOT items use MUST, NEVER, DO NOT. Verify Don't items contain no hedge language (should, ideally, consider, try to).
  - **Fail signal:** Any MUST/MUST NOT uses soft language, or any Don't contains hedge qualifiers.

